#: src/rust-2018/documentation/new-editions-of-the-book.md:1
msgid "New editions of the \"the book\""
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/new-editions-of-the-book.md:3
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.26](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.26-brightgreen.svg) for the final version of the "
"second edition"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/new-editions-of-the-book.md:5
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.31](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.31-brightgreen.svg) for the 2018 edition"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/new-editions-of-the-book.md:7
msgid ""
"We've distributed a copy of \"The Rust Programming Language,\" "
"affectionately nicknamed \"the book\", with every version of Rust since Rust "
"1.0."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/new-editions-of-the-book.md:10
msgid ""
"However, because it was written before Rust 1.0, it started showing its age. "
"Many parts of the book are vague, because it was written before the true "
"details were nailed down for the 1.0 release. It didn't do a fantastic job "
"of teaching lifetimes."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/new-editions-of-the-book.md:15
msgid ""
"Starting with Rust 1.18, we shipped drafts of a second edition of the book. "
"The final version was shipped with Rust 1.26. The second edition is a "
"complete re-write from the ground up, using the last two years of knowledge "
"we’ve gained from teaching people Rust."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/new-editions-of-the-book.md:20
msgid ""
"You can purchase [a printed version of the second edition from No Starch "
"Press](https://nostarch.com/Rust). Now that the print version has shipped, "
"the second edition is frozen."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/new-editions-of-the-book.md:24
msgid ""
"As of 1.31, the book has been completely updated for the 2018 Edition "
"release. It's still pretty close to the second edition, but contains "
"information about newer features since the book's content was frozen. "
"Additionally, instead of publishing separate editions of the book, only the "
"latest version of the book is published online. You’ll find brand-new "
"explanations for a lot of Rust’s core concepts, new projects to build, and "
"all kinds of other good stuff. Please [check it out](https://doc.rust-lang."
"org/book/index.html) and let us know what you think!"
msgstr ""
